# === Secrets / live config (extra belt-and-suspenders) ===
# .env is already covered above via the Python "Environments" block.
# Add explicit patterns for TARS-specific files that often carry real
# API keys so they can't accidentally land in commits even if dropped
# at the repo root or inside a crate dir.
secrets.toml
**/secrets.toml
api_keys.toml
**/api_keys.toml
.env.local
*.env.local
# Local TARS user config (one-off probe / bench setups; commonly hold
# real keys). The shipped tars-config docs use plain `config.toml` for
# the canonical example, so be specific: only `.local.toml` is ignored.
config.local.toml
**/config.local.toml


# Per-run log dumps emitted by downstream consumers
*.log.jsonl
